            <abstract id="ref1" label="Abstract">This is a copy of Moran's "libro grande" (1625-1650), and includes two versions of the grammar (in different hands), confessional materials, and a vocabulary of 500 words which has been added to the others. The first three pages are a narrative of Spanish missions (1689-1692) by Thomas Murillo. For description, see: D. G. Brinton. "Notice of some manuscripts..." 
                <emph render="italic">American Journal of Science</emph>, 2nd Series, 1869, v. 47, 222-230.</abstract>
            <langmaterial id="ref8" label="Language of Materials note">This volume is written in Spanish and Choltí.</langmaterial>
